Package com.rb.nonbiz.json

Class JsonApiPropertyDescriptor.CollectionJsonApiPropertyDescriptor

java.lang.Object
com.rb.nonbiz.json.JsonApiPropertyDescriptor
com.rb.nonbiz.json.JsonApiPropertyDescriptor.CollectionJsonApiPropertyDescriptor
Enclosing class:
JsonApiPropertyDescriptor
public static class JsonApiPropertyDescriptor.CollectionJsonApiPropertyDescriptor
extends JsonApiPropertyDescriptor
Tells us the type of property of a JsonObject in the JSON API, in the case where it is the JSON representation of a collection (Set, List, or array) of some Java data class.

We use a JsonApiPropertyDescriptor instead of just a raw Class so that we can represent things such as List<UniqueId<NamedFactor>> , i.e. where the value class inside the collection is not a simple class and is instead a generic, a map, etc.

      public java.util.Optional<JsonPropertySpecificDocumentation> getPropertySpecificDocumentation()
      Description copied from class: JsonApiPropertyDescriptor
      Per JsonPropertySpecificDocumentation documentation, it's used for cases where we want to attach context-specific documentation to a specific property of an object, vs. to the class.

      There are several cases where JsonApiPropertyDescriptors are nested. Example: a JsonApiPropertyDescriptor.CollectionJsonApiPropertyDescriptor of some other JsonApiPropertyDescriptor; e.g. a List of ClosedRange. Ideally, any extra JsonPropertySpecificDocumentation would only appear at the top level of this nesting (here, the List, and we shouldn't even be able to have more such JsonPropertySpecificDocumentation for the JsonApiPropertyDescriptors below (here, the ClosedRange). We will have preconditions for that, but we can't enforce it at runtime.
